content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Create chat buttons to enable customers to request a chat with an agent directly from your website.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create and customize chat buttons: Customize Application

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Before you create chat buttons:

Create skills. Each chat button is associated with a particular skill or set of skills.
To use custom images, create a Salesforce site and static resources.

From Setup, enter Chat Buttons in the Quick Find box, then select Chat Buttons & Invitations.
Click New.
Select Chat Button from the Type field.
Choose the settings for your chat button.
Click Save.
Copy the button code, and paste it on each web page where you've deployed Chat.

After creating the button, ensure:

The number of chats doesn't exceed the button's queue size.
At least one agent has available capacity and the required skills listed in the associated routing configuration.
title: Creating Customizable Chat Buttons for Service Cloud
